---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "April 4, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> {lastUpdated}</p>

  <h2>1. Overview</h2>
  <p>Pingr ("the App") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what data the App accesses, how it is used, and how it is stored.</p>

  <h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
  <p>Pingr does <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, or store any personal data on external servers. All data remains on your local device.</p>
  <p>The App accesses the following data from connected third-party services:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Notifications, repository information, and user profile</li>
    <li><strong>Gmail:</strong> Email metadata (subject, sender, date) for notification purposes</li>
    <li><strong>WhatsApp:</strong> Message notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Zammad:</strong> Ticket notifications and status updates</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
  <p>All data is stored locally on your device using SQLite. This includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Notification history</li>
    <li>API tokens and credentials (stored securely on your device)</li>
    <li>App preferences and settings</li>
  </ul>
  <p>No data is synced to cloud services or external servers operated by Pingr.</p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Pingr communicates directly with the APIs of the third-party services you connect. These communications are made using secure HTTPS connections. Each third-party service has its own privacy policy:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.whatsapp.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WhatsApp Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://zammad.com/en/company/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Zammad Privacy Policy</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Analytics and Tracking</h2>
  <p>Pingr does <strong>not</strong> use any analytics, tracking, or telemetry services. No usage data is collected or transmitted.</p>

  <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>7. Data Deletion</h2>
  <p>Since all data is stored locally, you can delete all Pingr data by uninstalling the App. No residual data remains on any external server.</p>

  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.</p>

  <h2>9. Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@pingrhub.com">info@pingrhub.com</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
